    <div class="col-xs-12 debate-date">
        <strong>24 March 1943</strong>
    </div>

    <div class="col-xs-12 debate-date">Volume 387</div>

    <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-12">
        <div class="container">
            <div id="debateContent">
                <div class="highlightedSearchTerms"></div>
                <div class="content-container">


<div class="content-item other-content">
        <!-- START statement -->
        <div class="statement col-md-9  content-container " id='contribution-91ec361d-42b7-42ea-9fe2-f2028af48cfe'>
            
<p class=""><em>The following Question stood upon the Order Paper in the name of</em> Mr. TINKER:</p>
        </div>
            <div class="col-md-3 hidden-sm hidden-xs right-column ">
            </div>
        <div class="clearfix"></div>
        <!-- END statement -->
</div>

<div class="content-item other-content">
        <!-- START statement -->
        <div class="statement col-md-9  content-container " id='contribution-2f5fc6ef-c139-453b-a30a-a0998106d432'>
            
<p class="">74. To ask Mr. Chancellor of the Exchequer whether he has considered the resolution sent to him by the Leigh Old Age Pensioners' Association asking for an increase of 5s. per week on the basic rate of all those old age pensioners who are not in employment; and will he make a statement.</p>
        </div>
            <div class="col-md-3 hidden-sm hidden-xs right-column ">
            </div>
        <div class="clearfix"></div>
        <!-- END statement -->
</div><div class="content-item" id="contribution-32d4777e-7480-4e61-9d3b-01f84c1efd5f">
    <div class="col-md-9 edit-fail-error">
        <div class="alert alert-danger" id="alert-32d4777e-7480-4e61-9d3b-01f84c1efd5f">
            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-info-sign"></span>The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-9 multiple-edit-warning">
        <div class="alert alert-warning" id="warning-32d4777e-7480-4e61-9d3b-01f84c1efd5f">
            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-info-sign"></span>This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.
        </div>
    </div>

        <div class="col-md-9 nohighlight member-container">
            <h2 class="memberLink col-md-9" id="member-link-32d4777e-7480-4e61-9d3b-01f84c1efd5f">
                Mr. Tinker
            </h2>
        </div>
            <div class="col-md-3 hidden-sm hidden-xs right-column ">
            <a href="#contribution-32d4777e-7480-4e61-9d3b-01f84c1efd5f" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
               data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
               data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1943-03-24/debates/64cb0d63-f788-4f12-8f1e-36a28099a6e6/QuestionsToMinisters#contribution-32d4777e-7480-4e61-9d3b-01f84c1efd5f">
                <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div><span class="share-text">Share</span>
            </a>
        </div>

    


    <div class="inner">
        <div class="col-md-9 contribution content-container">



<p class="">May I call attention to Question 74? I put this Question down to the Prime Minister. It was accepted by the Clerk at the Table and appeared on the Order Paper addressed to the Prime Minister. Since then I have received word that the Prime Minister is not answering it and that it is to be put down for answer by the Chancellor of the Exchequer. When a Member gets a Question past the Clerk at the Table—and it requires a little ingenuity to do that—and on the Order Paper, by whose authority is it addressed to another Minister? I believe that one of the Clerks or one of the secretaries of the Prime Minister has said that it should be addressed to the Chancellor of the Exchequer and that that is the reason for its being transferred. Has anybody authority to override the Clerk at the Table?</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                        <a href="#contribution-32d4777e-7480-4e61-9d3b-01f84c1efd5f" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-to-contribution-mobile link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
                           data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
                           data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1943-03-24/debates/64cb0d63-f788-4f12-8f1e-36a28099a6e6/QuestionsToMinisters#contribution-32d4777e-7480-4e61-9d3b-01f84c1efd5f">
                            <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div>&nbsp;Share
                        </a>
                    </div>

        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="clearfix"></div>
</div>





<div class="content-item" id="contribution-9f1757ee-fc8f-4b61-ab06-f9388d919f51">
    <div class="col-md-9 edit-fail-error">
        <div class="alert alert-danger" id="alert-9f1757ee-fc8f-4b61-ab06-f9388d919f51">
            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-info-sign"></span>The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-9 multiple-edit-warning">
        <div class="alert alert-warning" id="warning-9f1757ee-fc8f-4b61-ab06-f9388d919f51">
            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-info-sign"></span>This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.
        </div>
    </div>

        <div class="col-md-9 nohighlight member-container">
            <h2 class="memberLink col-md-9" id="member-link-9f1757ee-fc8f-4b61-ab06-f9388d919f51">
                Mr. Speaker
            </h2>
        </div>
            <div class="col-md-3 hidden-sm hidden-xs right-column ">
            <a href="#contribution-9f1757ee-fc8f-4b61-ab06-f9388d919f51" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
               data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
               data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1943-03-24/debates/64cb0d63-f788-4f12-8f1e-36a28099a6e6/QuestionsToMinisters#contribution-9f1757ee-fc8f-4b61-ab06-f9388d919f51">
                <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div><span class="share-text">Share</span>
            </a>
        </div>

    


    <div class="inner">
        <div class="col-md-9 contribution content-container">



<p class="">I understand that the Prime Minister delegates authority to other Ministers to answer Questions if they are not his immediate concern. That is <span id="1634" class="column-number" data-column-number="1634"></span> usually the practice. No doubt on this occasion the Prime Minister has noticed the Question on the Order Paper, and therefore the hon. Member has achieved his object.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                        <a href="#contribution-9f1757ee-fc8f-4b61-ab06-f9388d919f51" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-to-contribution-mobile link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
                           data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
                           data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1943-03-24/debates/64cb0d63-f788-4f12-8f1e-36a28099a6e6/QuestionsToMinisters#contribution-9f1757ee-fc8f-4b61-ab06-f9388d919f51">
                            <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div>&nbsp;Share
                        </a>
                    </div>

        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="clearfix"></div>
</div>





<div class="content-item" id="contribution-c0ee625d-75e9-4a24-8478-898bab810a50">
    <div class="col-md-9 edit-fail-error">
        <div class="alert alert-danger" id="alert-c0ee625d-75e9-4a24-8478-898bab810a50">
